# Mahjozly build plan (authoritative)

**Single source of detail:** `Mahjozly-Roadmap-Production.md` in this workspace. Product scope when needed: `Mahjozly-Master-Document.md`.

Do not invent extra phases, libraries, or features. Stay inside the **current** phase the user is working on unless they explicitly move on.

## Phase order (backend first, then frontend)

1. TypeScript foundation — 2. Project setup — 3. PostgreSQL + Prisma + Docker — 4. Logging — 5. Error handling — 6. Auth — 7. Business profile — 8. Services and addons — 9. Availability — 10. Public booking page — 11. Booking management — 12. Dashboard — 13. Redis auto expiry — 14. Jest — 15. Swagger — 16. GitHub Actions — 17. Deploy backend — 18. Next.js frontend — 19. Deploy frontend.

## Architecture (non-negotiable)

- Controllers: HTTP only — no Prisma in controllers; repositories own DB access.
- Services: business logic only — no Express APIs in services.
- Repositories: database (Prisma) only.
- All errors: global error handler — do not send responses directly inside arbitrary `catch` blocks.

## Workflow principles (from roadmap)

- Learn only what you need for the next step; one phase at a time — do not jump ahead.
- Build first, polish later; when stuck, debug the exact error (not new tutorial stacks).
- Separate repos eventually: `mahjozly-backend` and `mahjozly-frontend`; do not start frontend until backend is working per roadmap.
- Use the folder layout defined in Phase 2 of the roadmap (`config/`, `lib/`, `controllers/`, `services/`, `repositories/`, `queues/`, `workers/`, etc.).

For timing, estimates, “done when” checks, code snippets, and deltas vs older versions — read the matching section in `Mahjozly-Roadmap-Production.md`.
